WEBVTT

00:02.144 --> 00:04.945
So, anyway, last night on
video chat, I spent, like,

00:04.947 --> 00:07.381
20 minutes just staring
into Lucy's eyes.

00:07.383 --> 00:08.883
Oh, that sounds romantic.

00:08.885 --> 00:11.219
It was until I realized
the screen had frozen.

00:12.604 --> 00:15.122
Still one of my top three dates
of all time.

00:15.124 --> 00:17.475
So, are we ever gonna
hang out with this girl?

00:17.477 --> 00:18.843
I'd love that,

00:18.845 --> 00:20.845
but she's not really comfortable
around people.

00:20.847 --> 00:24.015
Yeah, I used to be
uncomfortable around people,

00:24.017 --> 00:25.733
but then I learned a trick.

00:25.735 --> 00:27.318
I pretend everyone I meet

00:27.320 --> 00:30.304
is a beloved character
from <i>Star Trek.</i>

00:31.323 --> 00:32.774
How's that been working
for you?

00:32.776 --> 00:36.277
Oh, like a charm, unnamed
crewman in a red shirt.

00:36.279 --> 00:40.531
Leonard, I may have
gotten you a job.

00:40.533 --> 00:41.949
I have a job.

00:41.951 --> 00:42.950
Yes, he does.

00:42.952 --> 00:45.319
He caters to
my every whim.

00:45.321 --> 00:48.656
No, in a couple of weeks,
Stephen Hawking's team

00:48.658 --> 00:50.825
is sending an expedition
to the North Sea

00:50.827 --> 00:53.461
to test hydrodynamic
simulations of black holes.

00:53.463 --> 00:55.780
One of their experimental
physicists dropped out,

00:55.782 --> 00:57.665
and I recommended you.

00:57.667 --> 01:00.468
Well, do you really think
I have a shot?

01:00.470 --> 01:02.436
Yeah, I've worked with Hawking.
I talked you up.

01:02.438 --> 01:04.188
He knows your research.

01:04.190 --> 01:05.388
I think this could happen.

01:05.391 --> 01:07.508
He knows-- Wow!

01:07.510 --> 01:11.178
Well, now, but do you
think that's a good idea?

01:11.947 --> 01:13.981
Uh, you know <i>Star Trek.</i>

01:13.983 --> 01:15.516
Should a guy
with no name

01:15.518 --> 01:18.119
and a red shirt really
go on an expedition?

01:19.454 --> 01:20.855
Hey, don't discourage him.

01:20.857 --> 01:22.490
This is a fantastic opportunity.

01:22.492 --> 01:23.825
No one asked you, Uhura.

01:28.547 --> 01:32.383
Would you like to hear a classic
Sheldon Cooper factoid?

01:32.385 --> 01:34.468
What do you think?
Great.

01:36.204 --> 01:39.223
I've been doing some reading
about vehicular safety.

01:39.225 --> 01:41.726
Did you know
that the highest number

01:41.728 --> 01:47.047
of drowning accidents happen
on or around boats?

01:47.049 --> 01:49.517
Interesting that you would
bring that up

01:49.519 --> 01:51.435
when I might go work on a boat.

01:51.437 --> 01:53.220
Well, that's the thing
about factoids--

01:53.222 --> 01:54.739
they're interesting.

01:56.558 --> 01:58.609
I know what
you're doing.

01:58.611 --> 02:00.745
You don't want me going
on this research trip

02:00.747 --> 02:02.496
because you're afraid
to be alone.

02:02.498 --> 02:04.699
I'm not afraid to be alone.

02:04.701 --> 02:06.284
On land.

02:08.002 --> 02:10.237
On the sea,
it would be terrifying.

02:12.007 --> 02:14.625
Because of all the drowning.

02:14.627 --> 02:16.627
Sheldon.

02:16.629 --> 02:18.629
Fine, no more drowning talk.

02:18.631 --> 02:20.548
I'll change the subject.

02:20.550 --> 02:24.418
Oh. Who do you think
would win in a fight--

02:24.420 --> 02:27.772
you or a shark?

02:27.774 --> 02:30.808
Look, I appreciate
your signature blend

02:30.810 --> 02:33.861
of concern for me
and incredible selfishness.

02:34.780 --> 02:36.397
If I get the chance to do this,

02:36.399 --> 02:38.699
there is nothing you can say
that's going to stop me.

02:38.701 --> 02:40.534
Very well.

02:42.371 --> 02:45.373
Things between you and Penny
have never been better.

02:45.375 --> 02:48.209
I hope four months apart
doesn't change anything.

02:53.649 --> 02:56.667
I should have opened
with that, huh?

02:56.669 --> 03:00.304
♪ Our whole universe
was in a hot, dense state ♪

03:00.306 --> 03:03.591
♪ Then nearly 14 billion years
ago expansion started... Wait! ♪

03:03.593 --> 03:05.259
♪ The Earth began to cool

03:05.261 --> 03:07.745
♪ The autotrophs began to drool,
Neanderthals developed tools ♪

03:07.747 --> 03:10.481
♪ We built the Wall
♪ <i>We built the pyramids</i> ♪

03:10.483 --> 03:13.084
♪ Math, Science, History,
unraveling the mystery ♪

03:13.086 --> 03:14.986
♪ That all started
with a big bang ♪

03:14.988 --> 03:16.061
♪ <i>Bang!</i> ♪

03:16.062 --> 03:20.062
<font color=#00FF00>♪ The Big Bang Theory 6x24 ♪</font>
