03:20.063 --> 03:25.063
== sync, corrected by <font color=#00FF00>elderman</font> ==

03:25.564 --> 03:27.698
If you look
carefully at Venus,

03:27.700 --> 03:29.150
you should be
able to see

03:29.152 --> 03:31.869
the International
Space Station pass by.

03:31.871 --> 03:33.538
Wow.

03:33.540 --> 03:35.073
Your friend
was actually up there?

03:35.075 --> 03:37.341
Yeah. He brought me back
a T-shirt that said,

03:37.343 --> 03:39.243
"My Friend Went to
the Space Station

03:39.245 --> 03:41.579
and All I Got Was
This Lousy T-Shirt""

03:42.864 --> 03:44.882
Did he take the
T-shirt to space?

03:44.884 --> 03:47.769
Nope. It's exactly
as lousy as advertised.

03:48.637 --> 03:50.705
Speaking of friends,

03:50.707 --> 03:52.807
they have been
asking to meet you.

03:52.809 --> 03:54.475
I was thinking

03:54.477 --> 03:56.043
maybe we could all
hang out sometime?

03:56.045 --> 03:57.478
I don't know.

03:57.480 --> 03:58.763
How many are there?

03:58.765 --> 04:00.715
Let's see. Six.

04:00.717 --> 04:03.901
That's pretty cool;
I have six friends!

04:04.903 --> 04:07.188
Kind of like Sinatra.

04:08.723 --> 04:10.741
Six strangers?

04:10.743 --> 04:12.727
That's a lot of pressure.

04:12.729 --> 04:14.745
Staring at me,
asking me personal questions.

04:14.747 --> 04:16.914
Like, "What do you do""

04:16.916 --> 04:18.533
"Where are you from?"

04:18.535 --> 04:21.786
"Why did you lock yourself
in the bathroom?"

04:21.788 --> 04:24.905
Okay, how about
you just dip your toe in

04:24.907 --> 04:26.340
and meet one of them?

04:26.342 --> 04:29.093
Will you be there?

04:29.095 --> 04:30.261
Of course.

04:30.263 --> 04:32.246
Well, that's two.
Three if you count me.

04:32.248 --> 04:33.914
Oh, this is getting out of hand.

04:36.468 --> 04:38.669
So, then, during
my afternoon shift,

04:38.671 --> 04:41.189
I spilled an entire tray
of drinks on myself.

04:41.191 --> 04:42.773
Oh, that's awful.

04:42.775 --> 04:44.275
Not really.
My shirt was soaking wet.

04:44.277 --> 04:46.761
I got, like, the biggest tip of my life.
Oh.

04:48.530 --> 04:51.616
So, listen, do you remember
when I said

04:51.618 --> 04:53.401
the similarities
of the equations

04:53.403 --> 04:55.870
of general relativity
and hydrodynamics suggest

04:55.872 --> 04:58.439
you could find the equivalent
of Unruh radiation

04:58.441 --> 05:00.024
in a large body of water?

05:00.026 --> 05:02.109
I thought I said that to you.

05:05.998 --> 05:07.965
Anyway,

05:07.967 --> 05:10.418
Stephen Hawking's team
is looking into that,

05:10.420 --> 05:12.720
and I've been invited
to join them.

05:12.722 --> 05:14.155
Wow, Hawking!

05:14.157 --> 05:15.389
Good for you!

05:15.391 --> 05:16.457
Well, it is.

05:16.459 --> 05:18.676
Just-- you know,
I'd be gone for a while.

05:18.678 --> 05:19.760
Well, how long?

05:19.762 --> 05:20.961
Three, four months.

05:20.963 --> 05:22.480
Whoa.

05:22.482 --> 05:24.482
When would you leave?

05:24.484 --> 05:25.483
Couple weeks.

05:25.485 --> 05:27.251
Wow.

05:27.253 --> 05:29.103
O-Okay, well,
I'll just come visit you.

05:29.105 --> 05:31.189
That's the thing-- you can't.

05:31.191 --> 05:33.124
I'll be on a ship
in the North Sea.

05:33.126 --> 05:34.475
On a ship?

05:34.477 --> 05:38.229
Aren't they afraid Hawking will
just roll overboard?

05:38.231 --> 05:40.498
Uh, he's not gonna be there.

05:40.500 --> 05:43.618
He's just sending a team
to research his theory.

05:43.620 --> 05:44.835
Oh, sure.

05:44.837 --> 05:48.489
Like when you send me
to kill spiders in your bathtub.

05:49.975 --> 05:52.210
Wow. Okay.

05:52.212 --> 05:53.827
Four months.

05:53.829 --> 05:55.413
Yeah.

05:55.415 --> 05:56.964
And I'm a little worried

05:56.966 --> 05:59.584
because things
between us have been so great,

05:59.586 --> 06:02.336
and I'd hate to do anything
that screws that up.

06:02.338 --> 06:04.338
Oh, sweetie,
if you're gonna screw things up,

06:04.340 --> 06:07.191
it's gonna be while you're here,
not while you're away.

06:07.193 --> 06:09.393
Oh.

06:11.747 --> 06:13.748
No. I mean, look,
you have to go.

06:13.750 --> 06:15.683
It sounds like
an amazing opportunity.

06:15.685 --> 06:16.951
And I'm just basing that

06:16.953 --> 06:19.654
on how much I didn't understand
what you said about it.

06:19.656 --> 06:22.323
Okay.

06:22.325 --> 06:24.992
I'll confirm the travel
arrangements in the morning.

06:24.994 --> 06:26.711
Okay. Good.

06:26.713 --> 06:28.796
I do have to ask
you one favor.

06:28.798 --> 06:30.064
Sure.

06:30.066 --> 06:31.249
Sheldon's nervous
about me leaving.

06:31.251 --> 06:33.084
Just keep an eye on him
while I'm gone.

06:33.086 --> 06:34.869
Oh, I don't know.

06:34.871 --> 06:38.589
Remember what happened when
I took care of your goldfish?

06:38.591 --> 06:41.909
Well, flush Sheldon down
the toilet and get me a new one.

06:45.180 --> 06:48.048
Really, you guys do not need
to throw me a going-away party.

06:48.050 --> 06:49.216
Are you kidding me?

06:49.218 --> 06:51.902
How often can you say
"Bon voyage" to somebody

06:51.904 --> 06:54.822
when they're actually going
on a <i>voyage?</i>

06:56.658 --> 06:58.075
Hello, Rajesh.

07:01.580 --> 07:04.081
Hello, Amy. Nice to see you.

07:06.735 --> 07:09.236
What can I say?
It's funnier with the accent.

07:10.255 --> 07:11.905
There's beer in the fridge.

07:11.907 --> 07:14.759
Anyway, you guys really don't
need to make a big deal.

07:14.761 --> 07:16.277
Leonard, you're being selfish.

07:16.279 --> 07:19.246
We need to give you a proper
send-off so we'll have closure

07:19.248 --> 07:21.932
when you die at sea
and crabs eat your face.

07:22.934 --> 07:25.186
Sheldon, sweetie, shut up.

07:25.188 --> 07:26.887
You know, one of the things

07:26.889 --> 07:29.273
that helped me get through
Howard being in space

07:29.275 --> 07:31.925
for so long was getting
married before he left.

07:34.913 --> 07:37.832
Bernadette, sweetie, shut up.

07:38.817 --> 07:40.067
Okay.

07:40.069 --> 07:41.485
I have a request to make.

07:41.487 --> 07:43.487
And now he can talk.

07:43.489 --> 07:45.456
I want to cut open your brain

07:45.458 --> 07:47.875
and see what the heck's
going on in there.

07:49.711 --> 07:52.880
The only person allowed
inside this head is Dr. Phil.

07:52.882 --> 07:54.782
Anyway,

07:54.784 --> 07:57.051
I-I spoke to my new lady friend
about meeting you all,

07:57.053 --> 07:59.003
and she thought
it would be easier for her

07:59.005 --> 08:00.171
to start with just one.

08:00.173 --> 08:01.922
Oh, gee, I don't know.

08:01.924 --> 08:04.124
My schedule's a little busy.

08:04.126 --> 08:06.510
Actually,
I was thinking Leonard.

08:06.512 --> 08:08.229
Oh. Thank you, Raj.

08:08.231 --> 08:09.347
I'd be honored.

08:09.349 --> 08:10.598
What the hell?

08:10.600 --> 08:12.900
I thought
I was your best friend.

08:12.902 --> 08:15.903
You are, but you've got
kind of a big personality,

08:15.905 --> 08:19.740
with your flashy clothes and
your Woody Allen swagger.

08:21.476 --> 08:22.943
You know,

08:22.945 --> 08:25.646
maybe she'd be more comfortable
meeting a girl first.

08:25.648 --> 08:27.081
Good idea. Bernadette?

08:27.083 --> 08:29.250
What the hell?!

08:29.252 --> 08:31.035
Well, you're very pretty.

08:31.037 --> 08:32.820
That could be intimidating
to another woman.

08:32.822 --> 08:34.988
Oh, yeah.

08:34.990 --> 08:38.042
Hey, you don't think I'm pretty
enough to scare your girlfriend?

08:38.044 --> 08:39.827
Calm down, Bernie.

08:39.828 --> 08:41.629
You're very scary.

08:43.465 --> 08:44.765
It should be me.

08:44.767 --> 08:46.016
Why?

08:46.018 --> 08:48.386
So you can make jokes
about cutting open my brain?

08:48.388 --> 08:51.004
A, that was not a joke.

08:51.006 --> 08:53.057
That was a sincere request.

08:54.393 --> 08:56.143
And B, more
importantly,

08:56.145 --> 08:57.695
I was the outsider
to this group,

08:57.697 --> 08:59.864
and I know how frightening
that can be.

08:59.866 --> 09:02.900
But you guys took me in
and made me feel loved,

09:02.902 --> 09:05.119
like I was family.

09:08.206 --> 09:09.907
Fine, I'll do it.

09:12.694 --> 09:14.862
So, after I started
dating Sheldon,

09:14.864 --> 09:17.364
I met Leonard,
and then everybody else,

09:17.366 --> 09:19.834
and they've all been
so wonderful to me.

09:19.836 --> 09:21.218
That's really nice to hear.

09:21.220 --> 09:23.370
Maybe next week,
we could all get together.

09:23.372 --> 09:25.473
Oh, Lucy, you don't
have to answer that.

09:25.475 --> 09:27.975
Don't put her on the
spot. She hates that.

09:27.977 --> 09:30.043
Am I right? Tell her
how much you hate

09:30.045 --> 09:32.263
being put on the spot.
Go ahead, tell her.

09:32.265 --> 09:34.849
Ignore him. He's a little
nervous 'cause he doesn't think

09:34.851 --> 09:36.567
I understand the severity
of your social anxiety.

09:36.569 --> 09:38.652
What the...?
Are you crazy?

09:38.654 --> 09:39.720
You can't talk
about social anxiety

09:39.722 --> 09:41.272
to someone who has
social anxiety.

09:41.274 --> 09:44.275
It makes them
socially anxious!

09:44.277 --> 09:46.110
Excuse me, but I'm
a neurobiologist.

09:46.112 --> 09:48.362
I think I'm a little
more qualified than you

09:48.364 --> 09:51.615
to understand what's not working
in your girlfriend's brain!

09:51.617 --> 09:52.750
Don't call her my girlfriend.

09:52.752 --> 09:54.452
We haven't discussed
whether or not

09:54.454 --> 09:55.953
we're girlfriend
or boyfriend yet.

09:57.405 --> 09:58.956
Now that it's
out there...

10:00.792 --> 10:02.560
...are you my girlfriend?

10:02.562 --> 10:03.694
By the way,
if you say no,

10:03.696 --> 10:06.297
I'll never be happy again.

10:07.282 --> 10:09.283
Not to put you on the spot.

10:10.869 --> 10:13.604
I think I have to go
to the bathroom.

10:17.692 --> 10:19.109
We might as well
go ahead and eat.

10:19.111 --> 10:20.861
She's not coming back
anytime soon.

