contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

10:29.956 --> 10:31.173
This is ridiculous.

10:31.174 --> 10:32.906
We're shopping
for a party.

10:32.908 --> 10:34.709
This store doesn't even
have a party section.

10:34.711 --> 10:37.912
Yeah, it does,
and here we are.

10:39.264 --> 10:40.965
You know, I have to say, Penny,

10:40.967 --> 10:43.134
I don't understand
why you of all people

10:43.136 --> 10:45.519
are encouraging Leonard
to do this.

10:45.521 --> 10:47.921
Well, I'm his girlfriend;
of course I'm gonna support him.

10:47.923 --> 10:50.141
Yeah, well,
you're his girlfriend for now.

10:50.143 --> 10:51.926
You know, maybe
you're not aware of this,

10:51.928 --> 10:53.928
but there is
a rich tradition

10:53.930 --> 10:58.199
of men at sea finding comfort in
each other's arms and britches.

10:59.952 --> 11:02.703
Honey, this is a big
deal for Leonard, okay?

11:02.705 --> 11:04.538
He gets to work with
Stephen Hawking.

11:04.540 --> 11:06.707
Who, by the way,
will not be on the boat.

11:06.709 --> 11:07.775
I checked it out.

11:07.777 --> 11:10.110
It's not that big
of an opportunity.

11:10.112 --> 11:12.480
And even if Hawking's theories
are correct,

11:12.482 --> 11:15.049
all they prove is
where the universe came from,

11:15.051 --> 11:17.969
why everything exists and
what its ultimate end will be.

11:17.971 --> 11:19.820
I mean, me?

11:19.822 --> 11:22.390
I'm interested
in the big questions.

11:24.142 --> 11:27.795
Oh, my God, Sheldon the genius
is jealous of Leonard.

11:27.797 --> 11:29.513
I'm not jealous.

11:29.515 --> 11:31.182
I'm just very unhappy

11:31.184 --> 11:33.017
that good things
are happening for him

11:33.019 --> 11:34.935
and not happening for me.

11:34.937 --> 11:37.655
Look, sweetie, this is
a natural thing to feel, okay?

11:37.657 --> 11:39.640
But just because good things
are happening to Leonard

11:39.642 --> 11:41.492
doesn't take anything
away from you.

11:41.494 --> 11:43.411
You know what? Let me
tell you a little story.

11:43.413 --> 11:45.446
Once there was a girl who worked
at the Cheesecake Factory,

11:45.448 --> 11:46.998
and she wasn't very good
at her job.

11:47.000 --> 11:49.617
It was you.
It wasn't me.

11:50.619 --> 11:51.669
But she was also an actress,

11:51.671 --> 11:53.404
and we were both up
for the same part

11:53.406 --> 11:54.455
in a toothpaste commercial.

11:54.457 --> 11:56.757
She got it. Look,
I was so jealous.

11:56.759 --> 11:59.326
But instead of ripping out
her fake blonde hair...

11:59.328 --> 12:01.429
You ripped out
your own fake blonde hair.

12:01.431 --> 12:03.097
I...

12:03.099 --> 12:04.849
looked her in the eye,

12:04.851 --> 12:07.168
smiled and said,
"I'm happy for you."

12:07.170 --> 12:08.836
Because that's what friends do.

12:10.272 --> 12:12.473
They lie
so they don't look petty.

12:12.475 --> 12:13.607
Yeah.

12:13.609 --> 12:14.942
How?

12:14.944 --> 12:17.078
Like this.

12:17.080 --> 12:19.880
I am so happy for you.

12:22.284 --> 12:23.751
Wow.

12:23.753 --> 12:26.404
No wonder you didn't get
that toothpaste commercial.

12:30.075 --> 12:31.859
Hey.

12:31.861 --> 12:33.294
Hi.

12:33.296 --> 12:35.629
I want to apologize
for Amy last night.

12:35.631 --> 12:38.031
She was completely out of line.

12:43.171 --> 12:45.639
Are you... are you
not speaking to me

12:45.641 --> 12:47.475
or did the screen freeze again?

12:47.477 --> 12:49.744
Amy wasn't the problem.

12:49.746 --> 12:51.762
Okay. I know.

12:51.764 --> 12:53.397
It was me.

12:53.399 --> 12:55.366
I-I pushed too hard. I'm sorry.

12:55.368 --> 12:56.817
Thank you.

12:56.819 --> 12:59.770
You know,
I-I've been thinking that...

12:59.772 --> 13:03.140
maybe meeting somebody
one-on-one is too intense,

13:03.142 --> 13:04.341
so...

13:04.343 --> 13:06.177
Friday night, my friends
are having a party.

13:06.179 --> 13:07.878
A party?
A little one!

13:07.880 --> 13:10.448
It's-it's a farewell
for Leonard,

13:10.450 --> 13:12.666
so all the attention
will be on him.

13:12.668 --> 13:15.419
If you wear something brown
and sit on the couch,

13:15.421 --> 13:17.471
they won't even know
you're there.

13:18.290 --> 13:20.374
I'm not sure.

13:20.376 --> 13:21.509
Oh, please?

13:21.511 --> 13:22.777
Raj.
Come on.

13:22.779 --> 13:23.911
Don't make me beg.

13:23.913 --> 13:27.131
And I'm from India,
so I know how to do it.

13:28.900 --> 13:30.634
Okay.

13:30.636 --> 13:31.752
Y... Thank you!

13:31.754 --> 13:33.270
Th-This means a lot to me.

13:33.272 --> 13:35.022
My friends are like my family.

13:35.674 --> 13:36.941
Unless you don't like them;

13:36.943 --> 13:39.210
in which case,
they're dead to me.

13:41.697 --> 13:44.264
So, have you ever spent
a long time on a boat before?

13:44.266 --> 13:46.200
Yeah.
Are you referring to the time

13:46.202 --> 13:49.403
we got stuck on the Small World
ride at Disneyland?

13:50.238 --> 13:52.156
Yeah.

13:54.810 --> 13:56.327
I'm proud of you, Leonard.

13:56.329 --> 13:58.162
Working out
on the North Sea

13:58.164 --> 14:00.948
for months--
that's really something.

14:00.950 --> 14:02.833
I know. As far as science goes,

14:02.835 --> 14:05.118
this is the adventure
of a lifetime.

14:05.120 --> 14:06.954
Maybe your lifetime.

14:06.956 --> 14:09.140
I went to space.

14:10.425 --> 14:12.309
It's not a competition.

14:12.311 --> 14:13.677
You're right, you're right.

14:13.679 --> 14:15.262
I'm really proud of you, and...

14:15.264 --> 14:17.148
I'm gonna miss you
when you're gone.

14:18.183 --> 14:20.701
And space beats water.

14:22.387 --> 14:25.406
Rajesh, I thought
Lucy was coming.

14:25.408 --> 14:27.408
She is. She's just running
a little late.

14:27.410 --> 14:29.743
You know how it is--
girls always fussing about

14:29.745 --> 14:30.978
their hair, their makeup.

14:30.980 --> 14:32.163
She'll be here.

14:32.165 --> 14:34.215
Just give it a rest, okay?

14:37.119 --> 14:40.221
Um, can I have
your attention, everyone?

14:41.673 --> 14:44.925
That's, uh, B-flat, for those
who don't have perfect pitch.

14:46.344 --> 14:48.712
I would like
to propose a toast

14:48.714 --> 14:51.799
to my best friend,
Dr. Leonard Hofstadter.

14:51.801 --> 14:55.553
He has been presented with
a wonderful opportunity,

14:55.555 --> 14:58.772
and I couldn't
be happier for him.

15:01.476 --> 15:02.693
Thank you, Sheldon.

15:02.695 --> 15:04.812
That must've been
very hard for you to say.

15:04.814 --> 15:06.697
Well, I mean it.

15:06.699 --> 15:09.349
I'm really happy
for you.

15:09.351 --> 15:12.203
And that's how you get
a toothpaste commercial. Cheers.

15:13.021 --> 15:14.755
Cheers.
Cheers.

15:16.491 --> 15:19.994
It was really nice of you
to try to be happy for Leonard.

15:19.996 --> 15:21.495
Mm. Thank you.

15:21.497 --> 15:24.197
It must've killed you
when I went to space.

15:27.752 --> 15:29.453
Oh, no.

15:29.455 --> 15:31.672
Buddy, you okay?

15:33.842 --> 15:36.176
Oh, man.

15:36.178 --> 15:38.262
What's going on?

15:38.264 --> 15:40.147
Uh, go ahead. Read it.

15:40.149 --> 15:42.349
"Raj, I can't come
to the party.

15:42.351 --> 15:43.684
"This is all just

15:43.686 --> 15:45.352
"too much for me.

15:45.354 --> 15:48.239
"I don't think
we should see

15:48.241 --> 15:50.441
"each other anymore.
Sorry.

15:50.443 --> 15:52.443
Lucy."

15:52.445 --> 15:54.111
Excuse me.

15:54.113 --> 15:56.780
Raj, I'm so sorry.

15:56.782 --> 15:59.016
Me, too.

16:01.704 --> 16:05.172
It did not kill me
when you went to space.

16:08.260 --> 16:10.761
Monkeys went to space.

16:15.384 --> 16:16.884
Well, here we are.

16:16.886 --> 16:18.686
Yep.

16:18.688 --> 16:21.105
I'm really gonna miss you.

16:21.107 --> 16:22.806
I'm gonna miss you, too.

16:22.808 --> 16:25.109
Penny, we're
in the red zone.

16:26.061 --> 16:28.696
The white zone
is for loading and unloading.

16:28.698 --> 16:31.198
We're breaking the law.

16:31.200 --> 16:32.483
Okay, there's no space

16:32.485 --> 16:33.901
in the white zone, so...
Anyway,

16:33.903 --> 16:37.237
we can e-mail, and I-I think
the phone connections

16:37.239 --> 16:38.455
are pretty good.

16:38.457 --> 16:40.291
All right, you have to get
out of the car right now.

16:40.293 --> 16:41.575
I'm not going
to jail for you.

16:41.577 --> 16:42.609
Would you just relax?

16:42.611 --> 16:44.878
Oh, I see a space
in the white zone.

16:44.880 --> 16:47.381
Quick, circle the airport.

16:47.383 --> 16:49.249
Did you bring enough inhalers?

16:49.251 --> 16:50.551
Yeah.

16:50.553 --> 16:51.802
And, uh, extra Dramamine?

16:51.804 --> 16:54.421
You remember what happened
on It's a Small World.

16:54.423 --> 16:55.723
I'm covered.

16:55.725 --> 16:56.957
Okay.

16:56.959 --> 16:58.676
Oh, dear Lord,
a police officer's

16:58.678 --> 16:59.927
glancing in our direction.

16:59.929 --> 17:02.396
We've been made.

17:03.264 --> 17:05.683
Calm down.
I'm getting out.

17:05.685 --> 17:07.401
I have something
I want to give you.

17:07.403 --> 17:08.902
Oh, Leonard.

17:08.904 --> 17:10.387
It's just a heart-shaped
locket with a picture of

17:10.388 --> 17:12.406
Leonard's face in it. He got
it at the mall on clearance.

17:12.407 --> 17:14.273
Now move, move, move!

17:15.109 --> 17:17.194
I love you.

17:17.195 --> 17:19.363
I love you, too.

17:21.700 --> 17:23.701
Don't worry, Officer.

17:23.703 --> 17:25.318
They just love each other.

17:25.319 --> 17:27.871
We're not smuggling drugs.

17:34.512 --> 17:35.846
Raj, it's Penny.

17:35.848 --> 17:37.214
Are you in there?

17:37.216 --> 17:38.932
Hang on.

17:41.469 --> 17:43.520
Hey. I'm just coming back
from the airport.

17:43.522 --> 17:45.439
I wanted to see
how you're doing.

17:45.441 --> 17:46.974
That's-that's very nice of you.

17:46.976 --> 17:48.842
Uh, come, come. Come on in.

17:48.844 --> 17:50.444
Can't stay long.

17:50.446 --> 17:53.714
I left Sheldon in the car
with the window cracked open.

17:54.866 --> 17:57.651
He's gonna go through
that activity book

17:57.653 --> 17:59.820
in, like, 30 seconds, so...

18:00.805 --> 18:02.639
Are you okay?

18:04.142 --> 18:05.309
No.

18:05.311 --> 18:07.194
Oh.

18:07.196 --> 18:09.362
I'm so sorry.

18:09.364 --> 18:10.497
No.

18:10.499 --> 18:12.249
It's my fault.

18:12.251 --> 18:15.302
You know, I finally found
someone who was right for me,

18:15.304 --> 18:17.938
and I-I drove her away.

18:17.940 --> 18:21.341
Oh, Raj.

18:21.343 --> 18:23.427
Penny, I...

18:23.429 --> 18:25.479
I miss her already.

18:25.481 --> 18:26.947
I know how you feel.

18:26.949 --> 18:28.198
I miss Leonard, too.

18:28.200 --> 18:31.551
What's... what is
wrong with me?

18:31.553 --> 18:34.438
Why-why can't I
ever have love?

18:34.440 --> 18:35.722
You will.

18:35.724 --> 18:38.025
No, I... I won't.

18:38.027 --> 18:39.576
I'm-I'm unlovable.

18:39.578 --> 18:42.579
That's just
the booze talking.

18:42.581 --> 18:44.064
No, it's not.

18:44.066 --> 18:46.784
I haven't had a drink
since last night.

18:55.210 --> 18:57.211
You're talking to me.

18:57.213 --> 18:58.896
I am.

19:00.216 --> 19:03.050
And now I'm crying for
a whole different reason!

19:03.052 --> 19:04.601
Me, too!

19:13.368 --> 19:14.988
So I-I guess
what I'm saying is.

19:15.013 --> 19:16.880
I get where Lucy's
coming from.

19:16.881 --> 19:18.631
That's great.
Do you want some wine?

19:18.633 --> 19:20.082
Uh, no, water's fine.

19:20.084 --> 19:22.852
Anyhow, I-I've been
thinking about it a lot,

19:22.854 --> 19:25.804
and-and I totally see
why Lucy did what she did.

19:25.806 --> 19:26.722
I pushed too hard.

19:26.724 --> 19:28.257
But you know what?
If I back off

19:28.259 --> 19:30.342
and give her enough space,
maybe there's still

19:30.344 --> 19:31.727
a future for us.

19:31.729 --> 19:34.013
Yeah, the funny thing about life
is that, you know, sometimes...

19:34.015 --> 19:37.149
Does he ever shut up?

19:37.151 --> 19:42.151
== sync, corrected by <font color=#00FF00>elderman</font> ==

19:47.861 --> 19:49.762
<i>...at least</i>
<i>my heart is starting to heal.</i>

19:49.764 --> 19:51.597
<i>Slowly but surely.</i>

19:51.599 --> 19:53.365
<i>And  how I cried.</i>

19:53.367 --> 19:56.268
<i>It was like a little, uh,</i>
<i>thunderstorm on my face.</i>

19:56.270 --> 19:58.003
<i>But I'm a man, okay?</i>

19:58.005 --> 20:00.172
<i>So I need to pull myself</i>
<i>together, pick up a pen</i>

20:00.174 --> 20:01.807
<i>and get it all out</i>
<i>in my journal.</i>

20:01.809 --> 20:03.609
<i>I mean,</i>
<i>it's not all bad, right?</i>

20:03.611 --> 20:04.877
<i>Having my heart broken</i>

20:04.879 --> 20:06.504
has allowed me to finally speak
<i>in front of you...</i>

20:06.529 --> 20:08.410
<i>so, you know,</i>
<i>it was a silver lining.</i>

